---
title: Pork Chops & Apple Rosemary Pan Sauce with Mashed Potatoes & Roasted Brussels Sprouts
description: These, friends, are not your average pork chops. In fact, our chefs gave ’em a restaurant-worthy makeover, transforming the everyday protein into something above and beyond. The chops are seared to perfection, then drizzled with an ultra-savory, rosemary-flecked apple pan sauce. The sides? Just as impressive. We’re serving up creamy mashed potatoes and roasted Brussels sprouts to round everything out. Get ready for maximum dinnertime deliciousness.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6051139552f025620b3fe9c0-bea9c14c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/pork-chops-apple-rosemary-pan-sauce-6051139552f025620b3fe9c0-c17a57c6.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
course: main course
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 640 kcal
  fat: 36 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 54 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 43 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 840 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pork-chops-apple-rosemary-pan-sauce-6051139552f025620b3fe9c0
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Halve and core @Apple{1}; dice one half into ¼-inch pieces (dice whole apple for 4 servings). Strip @Rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4).

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add diced apple and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring occasionally, until apple is slightly softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and @Water{½%cup} (¾ cup for 4 servings), and @Sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4) into pan with apple mixture. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to medium. Cook until apple is tender and liquid has reduced, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @Dijon Mustard{2%tsp} and @Butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted and combined. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Transfer to a #medium microwave-safe bowl{} and cover to keep warm. Wash out pan.

== Roasted Brussels Sprouts ==

Meanwhile, trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{18-22%minutes}.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

While Brussels sprouts roast, dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to #pot{}.

Mash with @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, @Butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), @Salt{}, and @Pepper{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Pork Chops ==

While potatoes cook, pat @Pork Chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in pan used for sauce over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

== To Serve ==

Divide mashed potatoes, Brussels sprouts, and pork between plates. Top pork with apple pan sauce.

> TIP: If sauce has cooled, reheat in microwave for 30 seconds or add back to pan with a splash of water; cook over medium heat, stirring, until warm.